                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d780">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1817: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-14T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 14, 1935—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 14—3:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>708. Your October 12, 2 p.m. I called upon Suvich this evening and made oral
                    representations on humanitarian grounds that they would abstain from bombardment
                    of the open cities of Addis Ababa and Diredawa and stated that my action was
                    similar to that of my colleagues representing Governments who had participated
                    in the conference of the Diplomatic Corps at Addis Ababa.</p>
                <p>As I left the Turkish Ambassador entered to make similar representations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
